cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.DC

This paper introduces a novel cognitive architecture for artificial intelligence in cyber-physical production systems. The paper focuses on the implementation of AI algorithms and their usage in production systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI. The paper also discusses the evaluation of the architecture, which involves the assessment of performance criteria, making cs.LG another likely category. The paper also discusses the modular design of the architecture, which enables the reusability and extensibility of pipeline components, making cs.SE a likely category. The paper also discusses the big data platform that implements the architecture, which involves virtualization and orchestration of the individual components and their communication, making cs.SY a likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the architecture using a real-world use case, which involves the processing of big data, making cs.DC a likely category.
